\begin{align*}
	R
	&= R_f -R_r \\
	&= \alpha \exp \left( - \dfrac{\Delta G - \sigma_s v^*}{k_BT} \right)
	-\alpha \exp \left( - \dfrac{\Delta G + \sigma_s v^*}{k_BT} \right) \\
	&= \alpha \exp \left( - \dfrac{\Delta G}{k_BT} \right) \exp \left(\dfrac{\sigma_s v^*}{k_BT} \right)
	- \alpha \exp \left( - \dfrac{\Delta G}{k_BT} \right) \exp \left(\dfrac{-\sigma_s v^*}{k_BT} \right)\\
	&= \alpha \exp \left( - \dfrac{\Delta G}{k_BT} \right) \left\{ \exp \left(\dfrac{\sigma_s v^*}{k_BT} \right)
	- \exp \left(\dfrac{-\sigma_s v^*}{k_BT} \right) \right\} \\
	&= 2 R_0 \sinh \left(\dfrac{\sigma_s v^*}{k_BT} \right)
\end{align*}
